DIGEST
SB 466 Original 2026 Regular Session Seabaugh
Present law authorizes expropriation of property for certain purposes by certain entities,
including the state, domestic and foreign corporations, limited liability companies, or other
legal entities.
Proposed law retains present law and prohibits expropriation under present law by any
foreign power, alien or corporation which is majority-owned by any foreign power, alien,
or alien corporation, as identified in federal regulations and in the database of the U.S.
Treasury, if the property to be expropriated is within 50 miles of a military base.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 19:2)
